Original programs:

1. udp_test_1_server.c: useful for testing hardcoded connections. This program
   will start up the petnet stack but does not rely on any TCP functionality
   being implemented. You can use it to test petnet's existing UDP
   functionality, and to start up petnet when developing and testing your
   hardcoded TCP implementation.

2. listen_server.c: useful for testing passive open. listens for incoming TCP
   connections on specified port. Accepts a connection, reads one message,
   sends one message, then receives data (without sending or printing anything)
   until the client closes the connection

3. simple_tcp_client.c: useful for testing active open. initiates TCP
   connection, then receives and echos data in a loop until the server closes
   the connection.

Additional programs:

1. simple_server.c: variant of listen_server.c that prints and responds to
   every received message, instead of only the first one.

2. send_server.c: variant of simple_server.c that only sends data (never calls
   recv)

3. recv_server.c: variant of simple_server.c that only receives data (never
   calls send)

4. tcp_client_close.c: variant of simple_tcp_client.c that only receives and
   echos one message and then closes the connection. This is useful for testing
   a client-initiated close from petnet.

5. tcp_no_data.c: same as tcp_client_close, but without the receive+send. It
   just opens the connection, sleeps 2 seconds, then closes the connection.
